1109
00:45:39,090 --> 00:45:40,440
Why the hormetic effect?

1110
00:45:40,440 --> 00:45:42,790
So what are some of
the ideas behind why

1111
00:45:42,790 --> 00:45:45,120
hormesis might happen?

1112
00:45:45,120 --> 00:45:47,990
So there are some theories,
and some controlled studies

1113
00:45:47,990 --> 00:45:50,930
showing that if you
irradiate cells very lightly,

1114
00:45:50,930 --> 00:45:52,820
they mount an immune response.

1115
00:45:52,820 --> 00:45:54,920
There are proteins
and things circulating

1116
00:45:54,920 --> 00:45:58,670
throughout your cells that
are there to repair DNA.

1117
00:45:58,670 --> 00:46:01,040
And if you stimulate the
production of those repair

1118
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:04,070
mechanisms, then the repair
will be more rapid given

1119
00:46:04,070 --> 00:46:06,150
the same amount of stimulus.

1120
00:46:06,150 --> 00:46:07,727
So in this case there are--

1121
00:46:07,727 --> 00:46:09,560
let's see-- I'm just
going to say proteins--

1122
00:46:09,560 --> 00:46:11,120
I can't say anything more--

1123
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:12,860
that will actually
travel along DNA,

1124
00:46:12,860 --> 00:46:15,950
looking for certain
types of kinks or breaks

1125
00:46:15,950 --> 00:46:17,240
and repair them.

1126
00:46:17,240 --> 00:46:19,670
If those repairs happen
before cell division,

1127
00:46:19,670 --> 00:46:21,500
then the mutation is avoided.

1128
00:46:21,500 --> 00:46:23,450
If you have more of
those repair mechanisms,

1129
00:46:23,450 --> 00:46:25,880
it takes a little bit
more energy to make them,

1130
00:46:25,880 --> 00:46:27,650
but you also have
less of a chance

1131
00:46:27,650 --> 00:46:32,160
of a mutation manifesting
itself past division number one.

1132
00:46:32,160 --> 00:46:34,530
So this is kind at the
cellular level idea

1133
00:46:34,530 --> 00:46:36,810
why might hormesis
be true, because you

1134
00:46:36,810 --> 00:46:40,110
stimulate your body's
ability to defend

1135
00:46:40,110 --> 00:46:43,237
against this kind of stuff.

1136
00:46:43,237 --> 00:46:44,070
And so there you go.

1137
00:46:44,070 --> 00:46:46,530
Cells can actually
signal each other.

1138
00:46:46,530 --> 00:46:51,510
So let's say a cell undergoes
DNA damage and can't divide.

1139
00:46:51,510 --> 00:46:52,980
These cells can
actually send what

1140
00:46:52,980 --> 00:46:55,920
they call kill signals
in the intercelluar space

1141
00:46:55,920 --> 00:46:58,320
to the nearby cells,
stimulating them

1142
00:46:58,320 --> 00:47:00,030
to mount some sort of response.

1143
00:47:00,030 --> 00:47:02,310
Either release
something or divide more

1144
00:47:02,310 --> 00:47:04,710
to make up for the dead
cells, which could be good

1145
00:47:04,710 --> 00:47:06,420
or which could be bad.

1146
00:47:06,420 --> 00:47:08,760
If you make more of these
DNA repair mechanisms,

1147
00:47:08,760 --> 00:47:10,590
that's probably a good thing.

1148
00:47:10,590 --> 00:47:12,300
If you stimulate
the nearby cells to

1149
00:47:12,300 --> 00:47:15,750
divide faster, well what are the
